\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 80. The Necromancers Device : undead, device, secret door\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 A scene of utter nightmare greets you in this chamber. Sitting in the middle of the large room is a machine of evil. Made from wood, bone and brass the device is covered in grabbers, conveyor belts, pistons and gears, all clanking away, while from somewhere inside a dull bell tolls occasionally. At least 20 feet square on each side, the machine glows with a blood red light in places, while necromantic imagery adorns it. Rotting limbs hang from various hooks all over the device, while body parts are fed into it by zombies that work from a pile of corpses. Severed hands swarm over over the device, pulling levers and adjusting dials, while skulls that have sprouted spider like boney legs oversee operation. At the far end, in a belch of foetid gas, a skeletal warrior steps out a picks up a rusty spear, joining the other undead that lurk here. Then they seem to notice you and move to attack.  
\i0\b \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\b0 \cf0 The device is of course highly magical, a mixture of both arcane magic and spells dedicated to the demon lord of undeath. Most clerics and paladins will consider a matter of the upmost urgency to destroy the device, which is the reason why the undead patrol the halls of the dungeon, ever searching for fresh victims to feed into the device. However it\'92s guarded by its latest creations, and is as powers of it\'92s own.  \
\
The device can shoot rays of enervating death magic once ever other turn. There are 1d4 rays, and hit anyone within the room who must make a save versus death magic or lose 1d4 points of strength. Anyone reduced to 2 or less strength collapses, unable to move themselves. Obviously heavily armoured characters will fall more quickly. Strength returns at 1 point a turn. \
\
The machine counts as creature in terms of trying to destroy it. It has an AC 4/16 HD 8 Hps 40 Saves as a 5
\fs18 \super th
\fs26 \nosupersub  level Cleric and is immune to mind affecting, poison, disease, death magic and take half damage from cold and lightning. \
\
In the room are 13 crawling claws, 4 skull spiders, 6 skeletons, 4 skeleton legionnaires, 3 skeleton archers and 4 zombies. \
\
Weapons and armour from those slain and brought back are used to equip the undead that are produced, however a pile of other belongings lie in a far corner. This includes 445 g.p. 1213 s.p. 6 pieces of topaz worth 35 g.p. each, a potion of invisibility and a rope of climbing.   \
\
