\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 81. The Hidden Bedroom : chests, traps\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 This hidden chamber contains an large bed, ornately detailed in death symbols. Against a wall is a desk and chair, dust covered by age while 3 oak chests are lined up next to it. The bed has a heavy dust cover over the bedding.  
\i0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0\fs26 Thandrak left behind this room as place to retreat to and as a store of minor unwanted items. The chests are each trapped with powerful necromantic spells. The first chest causes 3d8 negative energy damage if touch in anyway, even by a long pole. If the second chest is opened a cloud of black gas billows out, catching anyone in a 10ft radius. They must save versus death magic or be turned into a ghoul instantly. If the make their save they take 2d6 damage instead. The third chest\'92s trap is activated when it\'92s contents is disturbed. An evil ghost called Nukus Firriakin is bound to the chest and seeks to possess one of the party. That character selected at random must make a save versus spells. If they fail, the characters alignment is changed to neutral evil, and the ghost will seek to subtly destroy the rest of the party. The spirit can be driven out of the character, if the rest of the party work out they are possessed by a cleric turning the ghost as a wraith, which then will attack independently. If the character makes it\'92s save, the ghost tries the next character. If all characters make their save, the ghost flees, looking for another victim in the dungeon. \
\
